==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Webworm
<hw>Web"worm`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of various species of moths whose gregarious larvae eat the
leaves of trees, and construct a large web to which they retreat when
not feeding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The most destructive webworms belong to the family
<fam>Bombycidae</fam>, as the fall webworm (<spn>Hyphantria
textor</spn>), which feeds on various fruit and forest trees, and the
common tent caterpillar, which feeds on various fruit trees (see
<cref>Tent caterpillar</cref>, under <er>Tent</er>.) The grapevine
webworm is the larva of a geometrid moth (see <cref>Vine
inchworm</cref>, under <er>Vine</er>).</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wed</ent>⟦br⟧
